{"id":20531,"date":"2019-06-21T18:31:38","date_gmt":"2019-06-21T14:31:38","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/?p=20531"},"modified":"2025-03-22T09:41:46","modified_gmt":"2025-03-22T05:41:46","slug":"al-mundhiri-nifaq-two-faces-forked-tongues","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/al-mundhiri-nifaq-two-faces-forked-tongues\/","title":{"rendered":"Imam al-Mundhiri on Hypocrisy, Two-faces, and Forked-tongues"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><em>In the Name of Allah, the Gracious, the Merciful<\/em><\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Mundhiri recorded the chapter in his book Inspiring Hope and Inciting Fear:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u062a\u0631\u0647\u064a\u0628 \u0630\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0648\u062c\u0647\u064a\u0646 \u0648\u0630\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0646\u064a\u0646<\/p>\n<p>Discouragement to carry two-faces and to speak with a forked-tongue.<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Targhi\u0304b wal-Tarhi\u0304b 3\/602<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>Abu Huraira reported: The\u00a0Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u200f\u200f\u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0634\u064e\u0631\u0650\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0633\u0650 \u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0648\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0647\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0630\u0650\u064a \u064a\u064e\u0623\u0652\u062a\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064e\u0624\u064f\u0644\u0627\u064e\u0621\u0650 \u0628\u0650\u0648\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0647\u064d \u0648\u064e\u0647\u064e\u0624\u064f\u0644\u0627\u064e\u0621\u0650 \u0628\u0650\u0648\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0647\u064d<\/p>\n<p><strong>Verily, among the worst of people is one with two faces, he who comes with one face to these and another to those<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6757, Grade:\u00a0<strong><em><a href=\"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/10\/05\/hypocrites-two-faces\/\">Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/a><\/em><\/strong><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>Muhammad ibn Zayd reported: Some people said to Ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, \u201cWhen we had an audience with a ruler, we would speak to them differently than what we said after we left them.\u201d Ibn Umar said:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0643\u064f\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0639\u064f\u062f\u0651\u064f\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u0650\u0641\u064e\u0627\u0642\u064b\u0627<\/p>\n<p>We used to consider that hypocrisy.<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6756, Grade:\u00a0<strong><em><a href=\"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/21\/hypocrisy-speak-two-faces\/\">Sahih<\/a><\/em><\/strong><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>\u2018Ammar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0648\u064e\u062c\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0651\u064f\u0646\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u0650 \u0644\u0650\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0631\u064d<\/p>\n<p><strong>Whoever carries two faces in the world, he will have two tongues of fire on the Day of Resurrection.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4873, Grade:\u00a0<strong><em><a href=\"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/21\/two-faces-tongues-of-fire\/\">Sahih<\/a><\/em><\/strong><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p>Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said:<\/p>\n<blockquote>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0644\u0650\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0651\u064f\u0646\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0627 \u062c\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0644\u0650\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650 \u064a\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u0650<\/p>\n<p><strong>Whoever speaks with a forked-tongue in the world, Allah will make two tongues of fire for him on the Day of Resurrection.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Abi\u0304 Ya\u2019la\u0301 2746, Grade:\u00a0<strong><em><a href=\"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/21\/nifaq-forked-tongues-fire\/\">Sahih li ghayrihi<\/a><\/em><\/strong><\/p><\/blockquote>\n<p><em>Success comes from Allah, and Allah knows best.<\/em><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>&#8220;We used to consider that hypocrisy.&#8221;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"default","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"default","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","astra-migrate-meta-layouts":"set","ast-page-background-enabled":"default","ast-page-background-meta":{"desktop":{"background-color":"var(--ast-global-color-4